    "latest_release": null,
    "readme": "\u003ch1\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-nyx-with-ascent-in-container\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#nyx-with-ascent-in-container\"\u003e\u003cspan aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003eNyx with Ascent in Container\u003c/h1\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis project contains a Dockerfile and all necessary components to create a Docker container for Nyx.\nThe container is available on \u003ca href=\"https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/mswill/elwe_nyx\" rel=\"nofollow\"\u003eDockerhub\u003c/a\u003e, however these versions may not always be up to date.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-building-the-container\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#building-the-container\"\u003e\u003cspan aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003eBuilding the container\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Ascent actions can be changed by editing \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/m-s-will/nyx/blob/main/nyx/inputs/ascent/ascent_actions.yaml\"\u003eascent_actions.yaml\u003c/a\u003e.\nWhen finished with the customization, the container can be rebuilt by navigating into the source directory and executing:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ docker build -t \u0026lt;mytag\u0026gt; .\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Nyx simulation is being run during container creation and provides a Cinema database.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2\u003e\u003ca id=\"user-content-running-the-container\" class=\"anchor\" aria-hidden=\"true\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"#running-the-container\"\u003e\u003cspan aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"octicon octicon-link\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/a\u003eRunning the container\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAfter either pulling or building the container, it can be run by calling:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e$ docker run -p 80:80 \u0026lt;mytag\u0026gt;.\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e-p 80:80\u003c/code\u003e makes port 80 available on the outside which is needed for the Cinema viewer. We can then connect to it by visiting \u003ccode\u003elocalhost:80\u003c/code\u003e in our browser.\u003c/p\u003e\n",
